But the idea of the seat is more akin to what you and I might know as a county seat or a place or an area which exercises authority.

25:20.766 --> 25:23.890
And what this means is that it's not merely where mercy sat

25:24.002 --> 25:32.411
but it was where the activity of mercy would take place in the midst of God's people in Jerusalem and Zion is where mercy would be transacted.

25:33.993 --> 25:39.299
It's the difference between the king being approachable by the people and being with the people.

25:40.080 --> 25:49.010
Or think of it this way, we know where our president lives, 1600 Pennsylvania Avenue, Northwest, Washington, DC, 205-0-0.

25:51.513 --> 25:52.754
But we know he's there.

25:52.930 --> 25:57.339
at times and the Oval Office, or wherever the President might congregate.

25:58.321 --> 26:09.542
But isn't there a major difference between knowing where the President resides in D.C. and the President walking into your place of business, or wherever you might find yourself eating on a given day?

26:10.444 --> 26:15.474
Right, right if your doorbell rang and there was the President with a security detail and all the black doubt Tahoe is behind it.

26:16.386 --> 26:28.078
But the point here is that Jerusalem was not just where God's mercy and peace was found, but it was where it was intimately with God's people, where peace was transacted with God's people, where he was present with his people.

26:29.039 --> 26:43.474
And so beloved, you and I find peace this morning only because of our high priest, not by continual sacrifice, but by the once and for all sacrifice of the eternal spotless Lamb of God who takes away the sins of the world, who takes away your sins.

26:45.442 --> 26:53.996
You see, I think for the church peace foreshadowed here in these final verses, gives us a glimpse into the very hope of God's people through the work of Christ.

26:55.058 --> 26:59.064
Because there is not peace for us if there is no peace with God.

26:59.786 --> 27:03.532
There is no peace for us if there is no peace with God.

27:04.734 --> 27:09.842
And yet this morning we don't pray to Jerusalem, but we pray towards Christ.

27:10.082 --> 27:17.370
our great High Priest who is seated at the right hand of the Father and who will come again to make an established everlasting peace on earth.

27:19.072 --> 27:36.553
And so, the glory of our gathered worship is this work to which David delighted being called to worship, this work to which David devoted himself, unity, and this work that David desired.

27:37.293 --> 27:37.874
Peace.

27:39.234 --> 27:46.663
Friends, might this be our heart's desire as we worship all while that day is drawing near, when we will see our Savior face to face.

27:47.504 --> 27:54.954
For every Lord's day, the glory of our gathered worship is that we participate in half that glorious taste of heaven.

27:55.775 --> 28:01.362
So Lord's day, by Lord's day, we rejoice that we are one week closer to glory.

28:02.263 --> 28:06.248
Let's pray.

28:06.268 --> 28:08.050
Father, we thank You, O God,

28:08.962 --> 28:15.869
or that you would not only invite us to worship you, but Lord that you would even instruct us.

28:17.090 --> 28:19.192
You might even regulate Lord your worship.

28:20.513 --> 28:27.179
The Father that we might be given direction and how we might offer that which is pleasing in your sight and beautiful to your ears.

28:28.681 --> 28:35.627
And so Lord, we pray that you would stir us up all the more, that we would love being bound together or even here at Redeemer.

28:36.488 --> 28:38.290
Lord, to praise your glorious name.

28:39.554 --> 28:43.460
And so, Father, we ask that you would grant us all power and perseverance as a church.

28:44.421 --> 28:51.531
Oh, God, that you would call us to continually dwell in unity together, that we would rejoice that you have granted us peace.

28:52.893 --> 28:59.603
And Father, that others may look upon our fellowship, or that they might glorify you and praise you.

29:00.765 --> 29:03.088
Lord, we ask these things in Christ's precious name.

29:03.910 --> 29:04.170
Amen.

29:05.091 --> 29:06.994
Let's stand together and sing.

29:09.506 --> 29:10.195
Come on.

